00:08:19.670 --> 00:08:21.660 align:middle line:84%
And if there are
some family members--

00:08:21.660 --> 00:08:23.870 align:middle line:84%
you can forgive
some family members

00:08:23.870 --> 00:08:27.110 align:middle line:90%
who create a certain situation.

00:08:27.110 --> 00:08:29.360 align:middle line:90%
You have to remember-- OK.

00:08:29.360 --> 00:08:31.980 align:middle line:84%
Instead of going to judgment,
which is fear-based,

00:08:31.980 --> 00:08:34.110 align:middle line:84%
you've got to step
back and say, mm-hm.

00:08:34.110 --> 00:08:37.840 align:middle line:84%
What lesson are they
teaching me about myself?

00:08:37.840 --> 00:08:39.990 align:middle line:84%
And if I'm going to
jump in and judge,

00:08:39.990 --> 00:08:42.020 align:middle line:90%
I'm just as bad as they are.

00:08:42.020 --> 00:08:42.850 align:middle line:90%
Right?

00:08:42.850 --> 00:08:45.840 align:middle line:84%
So I often say to people-- you
know, they ask about karma.

00:08:45.840 --> 00:08:47.350 align:middle line:90%
What does karma mean?

00:08:47.350 --> 00:08:50.940 align:middle line:84%
Well, how people treat
you is your karma.

00:08:50.940 --> 00:08:54.760 align:middle line:90%
How you react is your karma.

00:08:54.760 --> 00:08:55.890 align:middle line:90%
Right?

00:08:55.890 --> 00:08:57.170 align:middle line:90%
It's really, really very true.

00:08:57.170 --> 00:09:00.040 align:middle line:84%
So it's really
being-- the many years

00:09:00.040 --> 00:09:01.150 align:middle line:90%
I've been doing this work.

00:09:01.150 --> 00:09:04.440 align:middle line:84%
And it really is taking
a pause and stepping back

00:09:04.440 --> 00:09:06.080 align:middle line:84%
and seeing if a
situation goes on,

00:09:06.080 --> 00:09:09.340 align:middle line:84%
a certain scenario-- where
is that person coming from?

00:09:09.340 --> 00:09:11.010 align:middle line:90%
Our first reaction is to judge.

00:09:11.010 --> 00:09:12.800 align:middle line:84%
But judgement is
really fear-based.

00:09:12.800 --> 00:09:15.910 align:middle line:84%
But if we step back and look
at it with compassion-- OK.

00:09:15.910 --> 00:09:18.900 align:middle line:84%
What is this person
telling me, treating me?

00:09:18.900 --> 00:09:22.250 align:middle line:90%
What is their backstory?

00:09:22.250 --> 00:09:23.140 align:middle line:90%
>>VAN PRAAGH: Huh?

00:09:23.140 --> 00:09:23.900 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:09:23.900 --> 00:09:26.760 align:middle line:84%
Because everybody you
meet has a backstory.

00:09:26.760 --> 00:09:28.450 align:middle line:90%
Everybody has a history.

00:09:28.450 --> 00:09:30.930 align:middle line:84%
And what will come to the
surface, you have to remember,

00:09:30.930 --> 00:09:35.007 align:middle line:84%
is always a combination of
their backstory, their values,

00:09:35.007 --> 00:09:37.340 align:middle line:84%
what they've been taught,
what they haven't been taught.

00:09:37.340 --> 00:09:39.010 align:middle line:84%
It's right there
in front of you.

00:09:39.010 --> 00:09:42.135 align:middle line:84%
And instead of judging
someone, just step in

00:09:42.135 --> 00:09:43.580 align:middle line:90%
and see what you can teach them.

00:09:43.580 --> 00:09:44.770 align:middle line:90%
How could you love them?

00:09:44.770 --> 00:09:47.470 align:middle line:84%
Treat them as you
want to be treated.

00:09:47.470 --> 00:09:50.970 align:middle line:84%
And really what it is-- it's
living a life of mindfulness,

00:09:50.970 --> 00:09:53.670 align:middle line:84%
being aware of what
you do to someone else,

00:09:53.670 --> 00:09:55.110 align:middle line:90%
what you say to somebody else.

00:09:55.110 --> 00:09:56.650 align:middle line:84%
And I always do
get by with that.

00:09:56.650 --> 00:09:59.274 align:middle line:84%
I always get by with a sense
of-- and I'm learning it, too.

00:09:59.274 --> 00:10:00.940 align:middle line:84%
I mean, every day
we're learning things.

00:10:00.940 --> 00:10:02.814 align:middle line:84%
In every situation,
we're learning something.

00:10:02.814 --> 00:10:06.390 align:middle line:84%
But I really do my best
to be mindful at changing

00:10:06.390 --> 00:10:09.450 align:middle line:84%
the scenario, changing the
energy around a person,

00:10:09.450 --> 00:10:10.630 align:middle line:90%
around a situation.

00:10:10.630 --> 00:10:13.800 align:middle line:84%
If I want them to be as
happy as I can be-- and let's

00:10:13.800 --> 00:10:16.830 align:middle line:84%
say they're depressed or they're
down or they're fear-based,

00:10:16.830 --> 00:10:20.000 align:middle line:84%
or whatever it might be,
if I go into that scenario

00:10:20.000 --> 00:10:23.470 align:middle line:84%
and I'm on that path, I'm
on that path for a reason.

00:10:23.470 --> 00:10:25.100 align:middle line:90%
I know there are no accidents.

00:10:25.100 --> 00:10:26.680 align:middle line:90%
I don't believe in accidents.

00:10:26.680 --> 00:10:28.420 align:middle line:84%
I know you don't
believe in accidents.

00:10:28.420 --> 00:10:29.200 align:middle line:90%
There are no accidents.

